<TITLE> Westmont chairman Tajul Islam sued for fraud </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com)A non-banking financial institution Monday sued Westmont Power Bangladesh chairman Tajul Islam Faruque on charges of fraud in loan payback. Tajul, the plaintiff of an extortion case against former prime minister Sheikh Hasina, has been accused of defaulting on paying back Tk 18.32 lakh to Fareast Finance and Investment Limited. According to case details, the financial institution's assistant manager Md Anwar Hossain filed the case with the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka after a bank had bounced a cheque signed by Tajul for payback. Fareast Finance and Investment served a legal notice on Tajul after the money was not paid out against the cheque. Metropolitan magistrate Md Emran Hossain Chowdhury recorded a statement from Anwar Hossain and issued an order for Tajul to appear in court on May 13. Tajul took Tk 5 crore in loans from Fareast Finance and Investment. Tajul had earlier brought extortion charges against Hasina in an April 9 case filed with Tejgaon Police Station. bd
